title: Natural Parenting
alt: On one hand, every single one of my ancestors going back billions of years has managed to figure it out. On the other hand, that's the mother of all sampling biases.
transcript:
[Cueball and Megan are standing with a baby in between them.]
Cueball: Oh man, we made a baby.
Megan: Don't panic. Don't panic.
Baby: Baby!Cueball: Parenting can't be that hard. Let's just do what comes naturally.[Beat frame.]Soon:
[There are now two babies in between them.]
Megan: Aw, crap.
